. The reported failure is API drift from 2.0.6 to 2.0.7, not missing setup: ArtifactResolutionException and ArtifactNotFoundException constructor signatures changed, so generated tests should use the 2.0.7 signatures or Artifact-based constructors. Prefer isolated/unit-style Maven core tests and side-effect-free MavenCli paths such as --version; if invoking real goals, use temporary directories/settings to avoid depending on the developer machine's ~/.m2 or network state.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Full Maven execution can read user settings/local repository and may try plugin or artifact resolution, making tests flaky if they rely on the host environment or network.\",\n    \"Several Maven 2 APIs are old internal-style APIs with version-specific constructors, so tests copied from 2.0.6 may not compile unchanged against 2.0.7.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0fece6a4331f1970016a41620206c881939911266d10e208dd\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2019, "output": 603, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26174, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782669818207, "responseId": "resp_0fece6a4331f1970016a4161fad820819391598fc5241350c1"}}
